">KEY WORDS </div><div class="t m1ae7 x27 h13 y1239 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Gospel. </div><div class="t m31b x63 h4 ye6b ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Anglo-Saxon, </div><div class="t m263 x2d h30 ye6b ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">godspel, </div><div class="t m7f7 x2e h4 ycdf ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;good </div><div class="t made x3 h4 ybbd ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">story&quot; or &quot;good news.&quot;) Translated in the </div><div class="t m12f4 x3 h4 y9c4 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bible from a Greek word that originally </div><div class="t m1be x3 h4 yfd7 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">referred to a reward to one who brought </div><div class="t m203 x3 h4 y96b ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">good tidings. Later employed for the good </div><div class="t m12a x3 h4 ya9c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tidings themselves. </div><div class="t m1ee5 x27 h13 yb90 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Three angels&apos; messages. </div><div class="t m479 x88 h4 yd2e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A term based </div><div class="t m372 x3 h4 y1471 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">on the prophetic messages recorded in Rev. </div><div class="t m9a3 x3 h4 yf56 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">14:6-11. Particularly used by Seventh-day </div><div class="t ma7c x3 h4 y11f2 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Adventists to describe God&apos;s final warning </div><div class="t m12ea x3 h4 ydd1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and last appeal to the world before the </div><div class="t m2db x3 h4 y20fd ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">close of probation and the second coming </div><div class="t m11e x3 h4 yb95 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of Christ. </div><div class="t m1bd8 x70 h13 y12d3 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Fear God. </div><div class="t m595 x57 h4 y12d3 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Fear&quot; is used in Rev. 14:7 </div><div class="t m628 x1c h4 yadc ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;not in the sense of being afraid of God, but </div><div class="t m70b x1c h4 y860 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in the sense of coming to Him with rever-</div><div class="t m4d6 x1c h4 y7